It allows to manage multiple screens in terminal

sudo apt-get install screen

open it with

screen

to get more info on all commands

Ctrl-a ?

to create a new screen

Ctrl-a c

to go back to the previous screen

Ctrl-a n

to divide the screen vertically

Ctrl-a |

the last symbol is a pipe

to move from a terminal to another

Ctrl-a TAB

to move from one to another

Ctrl-a "

to rename screen:

Ctrl-a A

to close a screen:

Ctrl-a k

to close a region (one of the sides of the termianl when you split it)

Ctrl-a X
